NEW STATEMENT:

938
Your Honor,

I humbly and unequivocally plead guilty to the charge of driving whilst disqualified. By entering this guilty plea, I acknowledge my responsibility and express my sincere remorse for my actions.

I stand before you as David Lambert, a 55-year-old individual with no criminal record, except for the recent disqualification from driving due to four speeding incidents. I understand the seriousness of these offenses and the impact they have had on the safety of others.

On the day in question, I made a thoughtless decision to drive to a supermarket, fully aware of my disqualification. I sincerely apologize for disregarding the law and disobeying the court's previous order. I am truly embarrassed by my actions and deeply regret the inconvenience or harm caused.

I recognize that my guilty plea is a significant mitigating factor in this case. By acknowledging my wrongdoing, I am demonstrating a genuine commitment to taking responsibility for my actions. I assure you that I fully comprehend the gravity of this offense and the need to make amends.

If given the opportunity, I am willing to undertake any necessary steps to improve myself and prevent any future transgressions. Whether it be attending a driving course or seeking additional education to address any underlying issues, I am dedicated to personal growth and ensuring that I never find myself in this position again.

Thank you for your attention and for considering the mitigating factors in this case.

Sincerely,

David Lambert

